snippet.textDisplay:
I'm pausing the video and doing each craft/ drawing I'll let you know how it goes.


Edit 1- Just finished the recreating art it took roughly 1hr bc it was a person


Edit 2- To finish an artwork I haven't (technically I haven't started this one but I've had it for literal years now and I really wanted to try it out) I did three adorable penguin felt things which took approximately an our and a half at the most, an hour at the least.


Edit 3- Annoyingly, for some reason, last night I decided to tidy every single drawer and box in my bedroom, and I looked for somewhere that wasn't tidy and found a box of books that I must have forgotten to do, so I did that and it probably took me 5 minutes. The good thing is, I found a knitting kit with an instructional book I got for Christmas so I'll probably do that tomorrow!


Edit 4- I don't have an art or craft book so...well, I have the knitting book I talked about in the last edit but I really don't wanna break it all out of the box and get the bundles of wool in a mess for a single look through of the instructions and ideas so sadly I have to give this one a pass. This took me 0 minutes except to type out the edit but I'm not counting that.


EDIT 5- THIS GETS FRUSTRATING NOW BECAUSE I'M SKIPPING SO MANY ONES BUT MY WEAKNESS IS HANDS AND IF YOU THINK FOR ONE SECOND THAT I'M WASTING AN HOUR OF MY DAY BEING ANGRY AT MY DRAWING THEN GO SUCK ON SOME SPAGHETTI! EVEN MORIAH SKIPPED THAT ONE SO DON'T JUDGE ME!P.S My failed first half-heated attempt took 10 minutes roughly and it is now in the trash.


Edit 6- I used some crappy watercolours that I rarely used and made three simple paintings, discarded one, and then my little brother came and wanted to get in on the action and he did two more so that was fun! They're currently drying in my kitchen and took roughly half an hour. Oh and my dog ate my hand ;-;
